13/09/2004
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic said Friday (10 September) that the government and police are willing to implement the entityâ€™s obligations to the UN war crimes tribunal in The Hague.
His comment was in response to local press reports that police have formed a special unit for apprehending war crimes indictees.
Also on Friday, a BiH court formally charged seven former Bosnian Croat officials with trying to establish unconstitutional Croat autonomy in BiH in 2001.
Those indicted include former BiH presidency member Ante Jelavic.
On Sunday, a military delegation travelled to Washington for meetings with counterparts at the US State Department and the Pentagon.
The talks are part of an agreement on bilateral military co-operation.
(Nezavisne novine, PBS BiH, NTV Hayat, AFP - 11/09/04;
RTRS, FENA, AFP - 10/09/04)
